<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3711848>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3–8. Semicerura bryophila sp. nov.: 3, labial palp (guards not shown); 4, macro- and s-chaetae on body; 5, ocelli and PAO; 6, apical part of tibiotarsus and claw III; 7–8, posterior (7) and anterior (8) sides of dens; Is-nae—two chaetae indicating the subfamily Isotominae, ms—ms-chaeta, ss—small s-chaeta, Semic.—two chaetae indicating the genus Semicerura." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3711848/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3711854>
    dc:description "FIGURES 20–27. Semicerura draconis sp. nov.: 20, macro- and s-chaetae on body; 21, ocelli and PAO; 22, maxillary head; 23–24, posterior (21) and anterior (22) sides of proximal part of dens; 25, apical part of tibiotarsus and claw III; 26–27, apex of Ant. IV, different specimens. ms—ms-chaeta, s—s-chaeta of middle size, ss—small s-chaeta." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3711854/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

